TEXT -2288 1640 Left 2 !;.ac dec 100 2.5e6 10e6\n;.op;\n;.noise V(out2) V2 dec 500 1e6 10e6\n.tran 0 300u 0\n.model switch1 SW (Ron=1e-3 Roff=100Meg Vt=0.5)
TEXT 32 600 Left 2 ;Resonant filter that has\nan impedance of 52.3 \nOhms, as per the datasheet
TEXT 632 1096 Left 2 !.param freq 4e6\n;.step param freq 3.8e6 4e6 2e5
TEXT 16 1816 Left 2 ;4MHz resonant filter\nSwitched frequency should not be affected significantly in amplitude, only in phase.\nMaybe do 3.9MHz
TEXT 1240 1232 Left 2 ;Mixer model
TEXT 1616 1032 Left 2 ;Amp and low pass to filter out carrier\nand 2x carrier frequency
TEXT 952 1240 Left 2 ;Input to LO
TEXT 616 1224 Left 2 ;Input to IN
TEXT 1880 1392 Left 2 ;Switch
TEXT 112 936 Left 2 ;<--------------------------------------------------------------------- For these switches, use just one double pole single throw switch --------------------------------------------------------------------->
TEXT -2168 248 Left 2 ;Make this an SMA connector
TEXT -32 1544 Left 2 ;DC bias
TEXT 1256 448 Left 2 ;Use whichever diode has a footprint
TEXT 1032 1472 Left 2 ;For the mixer:\nPin 1: LO- is ground\nPin 2: EN is 3V (VDD)\nPin 3: IN+ is the input indicated with "Input to IN," also called vi1.\n            Note the 30 Ohms Rin1 is the internal resistance and should not be included\nPin 4: IN- is ground\nPin 5: OUT- is ground\nPin 6: OUT+ is the output that goes to the noninverting input of the next amplifier\nPin 7: VCC is 3V (VDD)\nPin 8: LO+ is the input indicated with "Input to LO," also called vi2.\n            As with the other input, the 180 Ohms is internal resistance, so do not include it.\nAll of this above will replace the behavioral model, so the current source and 220 Ohm resistor in the model should not be in the schematic
TEXT -144 1216 Left 2 ;R24, R25, and R26 are jumpers to allow us to bypass the inverter stage
RECTANGLE Normal -1680 816 -2272 208 2
